parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The intermittent engine stalling can cause the vehicle to suddenly lose power, leading to potential accidents, especially when driving at high speeds or in heavy traffic.
symptoms: The engine stalls without warning
often when slowing down or coming to a stop
and can be restarted by shifting into neutral and turning the key; the vehicle may jerk or hesitate before stalling.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the air conditioning compressor can cause the system to shut off intermittently, leading to discomfort and distraction for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: The air conditioning system shuts off and restarts randomly
resulting in intermittent cooling performance; in some cases
the compressor may need to be replaced.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The rattling noise from the engine can be a sign of a more serious underlying problem, potentially leading to engine damage or failure if left unchecked.
symptoms: A rattling sound is heard from the engine while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The presence of unidentified vapors in the vehicle can be a safety concern, potentially causing dizziness, lightheadedness, or other health issues for the driver and passengers.
symptoms: Unidentified vapors are detected in the vehicle
causing the driver to feel lightheaded or dizzy.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Premature Brake Rotor Wear and Warping
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake rotor wear and warping can lead to extended stopping distances, vibrations, and shaking, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Vibrations or shaking when applying the brakes
extended stopping distances
uneven brake pad wear
warped rotors
and low-speed shuddering or vibration.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake system failure can cause the vehicle to take longer to stop, leading to accidents or near-miss situations.
symptoms: Vehicle takes a long way to stop when applying the brakes
brakes have to be pressed all the way to the floor to slow down
and feeling of the vehicle braking without pressing the brake pedal.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Uneven brake pad wear can lead to premature brake rotor wear, vibrations, and extended stopping distances, increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: Uneven brake pad wear
outside brake pad worn down to the squealer
and inside brake pad showing little wear.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Power Steering Rack and Pinion Assembly Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the power steering rack and pinion assembly can cause loss of steering control, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Steering wheel shakes or vibrates
grinding or growling noise when turning
difficulty steering
tight steering
noise coming from the steering wheel when on bumpy roads
vibration coming from the steering wheel at low speeds
transaction control light comes on when making left turns
car does not keep straight when driving straight down the road.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the steering column can cause the steering wheel to come loose or fall off, making it difficult or impossible to steer the vehicle, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: Steering wheel comes loose or falls off
constant adjustment of the steering wheel is required.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the electrical system can cause the alarm to go off, headlights and horn to malfunction, which can be distracting and potentially lead to accidents.
symptoms: Alarm goes off intermittently
headlights and horn malfunction.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ignition switch can cause the vehicle to stall or shut off while in motion, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The key switch suddenly turns back
the vehicle shuts off
no braking or steering is possible
the ignition switch is stuck
the key does not turn in the ignition.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the electrical system can cause the lights to flicker or come on by themselves, draining the battery and potentially leading to a loss of power or stalling while in motion.
symptoms: Lights come on and flicker by themselves
even when the car is off
the smell of burned rubber is present
the battery is drained.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling of the vehicle can cause a loss of control and increase the risk of accidents, especially if it occurs in traffic.
symptoms: The vehicle stalls once a day
almost every day
in traffic
the vehicle sometimes doesn't quite stall and catches itself
launching forward a few feet.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The design of the horn sensor can make it difficult to access in emergency situations, potentially leading to a delay in responding to hazardous situations.
symptoms: The horn sensor is not easily located
it is difficult to access when the driver is unable to look down at the wheel to find the "sweet spot" to engage the horn.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel rail system can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires, engine damage, and potentially result in loss of life.
symptoms: Fuel leaks
fuel smell
difficulty starting the engine
engine turning over but not starting
fuel rail splitting
fuel pressure regulator failure
faulty fuel gauge
check engine light.
